      "title": "ZMongo Workflow Guide",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# ZMongo Workflow Guide\n\nThis workflow demonstrates the recommended way to use the current ZMongo nodes inside ComfyUI.\n\n## What this template shows\n1. Configure the shared ZMongo connection.\n2. Browse records from a collection.\n3. Inspect the selected record JSON.\n4. Extract a field using the field selector.\n5. Select a record range using the record loop node.\n6. Save the selected field values to files.\n\n## Recommended usage pattern\n- Use **ZMongoConfigNode** first to confirm your database connection.\n- Use **ZMongoDatabaseBrowserNode** when you want to inspect real records and discover fields.\n- Use **ZMongoFieldSelector** to pick a field from a selected record.\n- Use **ZMongoRecordLoopNode** when you want one record, a range of records, or a field-value list for batch export.\n- Use **ZMongoSaveTextNode** to save one value or a JSON list of values to the ComfyUI output folder.\n\n## Typical field names\nFor OCR or document workflows, the most common field is usually:\n- `text`\n\n## Important note about ranges\nThe record loop node returns data according to its `emit_mode`. If you want to save multiple field values at once, use:\n- `emit_mode = list_of_prompts`\n\nThe save node can then split that JSON list into separate files when:\n- `save_layout = separate file per item`\n\n## Expected output folder\nSaved files will go into the ComfyUI output directory."
      ],
      "color": "#2a2f38",
      "bgcolor": "#3a4250"
    },
