      "title": "How To Browse And Discover Fields",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Browsing workflow\n\nUse the database browser to inspect real records from the collection before building downstream logic.\n\n### Key controls\n- **mongo_uri**: database URI\n- **database_name**: database to inspect\n- **collection_name**: collection to inspect\n- **limit**: how many records to preview\n- **select_index**: which record to fetch as the selected record\n\n### Recommended first step\nStart with:\n- collection: `ocr_docs`\n- limit: `20`\n- select_index: `1`\n\nThen inspect:\n- `selected_record_json`\n- `record_list_summary`\n- `selected_index_out`\n\nAfter that, connect `selected_record_json` into **ZMongoFieldSelector** and choose a field like `text`."
      ],
      "color": "#2f3a2a",
      "bgcolor": "#45563d"
    },
