      "title": "How To Use The Record Loop Node",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Record loop workflow\n\nUse the record loop node when you want to select one record or many records for export or downstream generation.\n\n### Recommended meanings of the current fields\n- **mode**\n  - `single` = one record\n  - `range` = a record range\n  - `all` = all matching records\n  - `batch` = first batch from the selected range\n  - `random_single` = one random record\n  - `random_batch` = random batch of records\n\n- **field_path** = main field to extract, usually `text`\n- **fallback_field_paths** = backup field names\n- **emit_mode**\n  - `prompt_text` = one field value\n  - `record_json` = one record as JSON\n  - `record_and_prompt` = one record plus one field value\n  - `list_of_records` = JSON list of records\n  - `list_of_prompts` = JSON list of field values\n\n### Recommended batch export setting\nTo save a range of `text` values to files, use:\n- `mode = range`\n- `start_index = 1`\n- `end_index = 4`\n- `field_path = text`\n- `emit_mode = list_of_prompts`\n\nThen connect the second output into **ZMongoSaveTextNode**."
      ],
      "color": "#3a2f2a",
      "bgcolor": "#5b463f"
    },
